The third file, @file{os-flute-2.ly} also reads the definitions of the
first (@file{os-music.ly}), and defines the @code{\score} block for the
second flute part.

@example
\include "os-music.ly";
\include "paper16.ly";

\score @{
  \context Staff <
    \property Staff.midiInstrument = #"flute"
    \global
    \Key
